Feature: provisioning the broker vault with the real credentials is a single, explicit, human-gated paste performed once

  SB-6 provisioning arm (PDR-017 §3 SB-6; ADR-028 D1/ADR-026 D4). The one unavoidable
  out-of-band step: a human reads the real Claude OAuth tokens and the real GitHub
  credential and stores them in the broker vault once. The spike proved provisioning is
  scriptable down to the single token-paste (owner register, service/agent/token mint,
  ca fetch are CLI-doable). This pins that provisioning is an explicit human-gated
  precondition, not an automated step. Lead-owned integration check against the real
  broker.

@scenario_hash:4ecd3b661ddf4713 @lead_integration:agent-vault-broker
  Scenario: the broker vault is provisioned by exactly one human-gated paste of the real credentials
    Given a running agent-vault broker with an empty vault
    When the real Claude OAuth credential and the real GitHub credential are loaded into the vault
    Then the only human-gated step performed was a single out-of-band paste of the real credentials
    And after that paste the vault holds the real Claude OAuth credential and the real GitHub credential
